-- Rare Earth Won't Be Bargaining Chip, China Industry Ministry Official Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-28T02:23:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/china-won-t-use-rare-earths-as-a-bargaining-chip-ministry-official-says.html
China won’t use rare earths as a
bargaining chip, said Zhu Hongren, chief engineer of the
Ministry of Industry and Information Technology. Zhu said
China’s rare-earth exports account for 90 percent of the world
total, he said at a briefing in Beijing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
